{
  "text": "Ten undamaged shade leaves were collected from each tree in mid summer, and examined for area, number of lobes, length/width proportion, leaf mass per area (LMA), number of stellate-hair clusters, length of stellate hairs, and the presence (or absence) of solitary and short hairs, according to [CITATION_1] . These traits co-varied little with each other [CITATION_2] .",
